From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Fujisan Developer <fujisan@atari>
Date: Sun, 8 Feb 2025 00:00:00 -0800
Subject: [PATCH] Give BINLOAD priority over NetSIO during XEX loading

When NetSIO is enabled, SIO traffic was unconditionally routed to FujiNet-PC.
This prevented BINLOAD from loading XEX files via TCP because D1: commands
went to FujiNet (serving the config disk) instead of the local BINLOAD loader.

Fix: Use local SIO handling when BINLOAD_start_binloading is true. During
XEX load, D1: is handled by BINLOAD_LoaderStart which feeds XEX data from
the local file. After load completes, NetSIO resumes for N:, P:, etc.

This allows media.load_xex via TCP to work correctly when NetSIO/FujiNet
is enabled, matching Altirra's behavior of loading XEX with FujiNet features
available.
---
 src/sio.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/sio.c b/src/sio.c
index 0000000..1111111 100644
--- a/src/sio.c
+++ b/src/sio.c
@@ -1673,7 +1673,7 @@ void SIO_PutByte(int byte)
 {
 #ifdef NETSIO
-	if (netsio_enabled)
+	if (netsio_enabled && !BINLOAD_start_binloading)
 	{
 		NetSIO_PutByte(byte);
 		return;
@@ -1831,7 +1831,7 @@ int SIO_GetByte(void)
 	int byte = 0;
 
 #ifdef NETSIO
-	if (netsio_enabled)
+	if (netsio_enabled && !BINLOAD_start_binloading)
 		return NetSIO_GetByte();
 #endif /* NETSIO */
 